	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I just happened to pop in here, because of a post a lvl 10 made.  Kinda shocked me alot of the negative comments made about this spell.  I'm lvl 29 at the moment, and have taken my time leveling, so it's been a while.  But I used this spell well into lvl 17.  This is a excelent spell. When I used it was from 12-17.  First, haveing a tough tank who is dealing some damage helps alot.  A decent Bard has a high agro rate as well. ..  let the tank hammer into a mob for a while..  get it's full attention.  Now if a tank has done some decent damage to a single mob.. (atleast 15 seconds) and you drop a AoE .. gues what?  a high chance that all the other MoBs beating on him who he hasn't touched, WON'T go after you.. because his agro lvl is actually higher then the damage you've dealt.  This works even better if you don't start out with your strongest AE) .. so anyways.. from lvl 12-17 use Column of Frost and The Fire Rain spell you get at 12.  They work BEUTIFULLY together.. you'll never see mobs go down faster.  Those 2 spell combinations honestly, as funny as it sounds, had me feeling bad at times for the other caster in my groups..  as I was really carrying the battles.  The reason that 2 spell combination works so great, is because MoBs do develop tolerances .. if you keep hitting them with fire.. eventually they get kinda use to it, and don't take full or as much damage.. if you cool them down before you reheat em.. they do the pain dance much better.  I was able to chain cast that combination of spells on the Orc's at the orc highway.. and did very well.   Worked well on the derv in Ro as well.<BR>

				</font>
			</td>

